  <p>
    When you sell a home on a septic system, there's one question you can count on: a serious buyer,
    or their inspector, will want to know the condition of the system they can't see. You can let that
    question surface at the worst possible moment — mid-negotiation, on a deadline — or you can answer
    it before you list. Sellers who choose the second path tend to have calmer sales and more
    leverage.
  </p>

